OL,3,CHastings MP calls for bio-bead ban
OL,4,Cwhile Eastbourne clean-up continues
OL,6,FRye Harbour Nature Reserve is one of
OL,7,Fthe largest and most important
OL,8,Fwildlife sites in England, home to
OL,9,Fmore than 4,355 species of plants and
OL,10,Fanimals including 300 that are rare or
OL,11,Fendangered. The discovery of the beads
OL,12,Fin the saltmarsh at the reserve caused
OL,13,Fgreat upset amongst wildlife lovers in
OL,14,FSussex and beyond, i
OL,16,FThe Environment Secretary has already
OL,17,Fcalled for a full investigation, as
OL,18,Fthe Director of Conservation at Sussex
OL,19,FWildlife Trust said the impact of
OL,20,Fbioplastics on birds is incredible
OL,21,Fharmful.
